[32m│[0m goes to server logs/stdout rather than response                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 2. **WAF/filtering**: Server may have runtime protections detecting and      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m blocking `os` module imports                                                 [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 3. **Serialization vs execution**: Server might extract specific fields from [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m deserialized objects without executing arbitrary code                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 4. **Timeout/exception handling**: Command execution may trigger exceptions  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m that are caught and silently reset the cookie                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
